==Abstract==

This BMIP describes a specification that how to use arrays in contracts.

==Motivation==

This standard will allow arrays in a smart contract. Through a standard type, the contract will be able to use mutable sequences and process data in batches. This standard will simplify the implementation of complex contracts.

==Specification==

Arrays are mutable sequences which are formed by placing a comma-separated list of expressions in square brackets. The indices of arrays are zero-based and any type of elements can be arrays' elements. 

Define:
{|
| '''Type''' || '''Define''' || '''Example'''
|-
| Fixed-size array || define identifier : TypeName <nowiki>[Size] = [expr1, expr2, ..., exprSize]</nowiki> || define value : Integer <nowiki>[5] = [amount1, amount2, ..., amount5]</nowiki>
|-
| Dynamically-sized array || define identifier : TypeName <nowiki>[] = [expr1, expr2, ..., exprSize]</nowiki> || define value : Integer <nowiki>[] = [amount1, amount2, ..., amount5]</nowiki>
|}

TypeName: Integer, Amount, Boolean, String, Hash, Asset, PublicKey, Signature, Program.

Functions:
{|
| '''Name''' || '''Meaning'''
|-
| length || Yield the length of the array.
|-
| push || Removes and Returns the last element in the array.
|}

